{"slug": "best-platforms-to-buy-sell-ai-domains-2026", "title": "Best Platforms to Buy and Sell .ai Domains in 2026 (Ranked)", "date": "2026-04-14", "description": "The best platform for .ai domain trading in 2026 depends on your goal: Sedo leads for high-value premium sales and brand recognition, Namecheap dominates volume with 2,514 recorded sales (63% of the Namepros marketplace), Afternic excels at wholesale distribution to a broad buyer network, and GoDaddy Auctions offers massive traffic but charges higher fees. For most sellers, listing on two or more platforms simultaneously is the optimal strategy.", "readTime": "14 min read", "author": "NameBuzz Research Team", "schema_faq": "{\"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"FAQPage\", \"mainEntity\": [{\"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"Which platform has the lowest fees for selling .ai domains?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"Dan.com has the lowest commission at 3%, followed by Namecheap at 4.5% and Afternic at 3\\u20135%. However, platforms with higher fees like Sedo (8\\u201315%) often attract buyers willing to pay significantly more for premium domains, so calculate your expected net on each platform before deciding where to list.\"}}, {\"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"Can I list my .ai domain on multiple platforms at the same time?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"Yes, and for most sellers this is the recommended strategy. You can list on Namecheap and simultaneously opt into the Afternic distribution network, or list on both Sedo and Afternic. Just make sure your pricing is consistent across platforms to avoid confusing buyers.\"}}, {\"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"What is the average sale price for a .ai domain?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"Based on 3,989 Namepros-recorded .ai domain sales, the median sale price is $2,215 and the mean is $9,433. The gap reflects a heavy right tail of high-value sales. 90% of all .ai domain sales fall below $20,000.\"}}, {\"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"Is Sedo or GoDaddy better for selling .ai domains?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"It depends on the domain value. For domains under $10,000, GoDaddy's traffic advantage helps find buyers faster. For domains above $50,000, Sedo's high-net-worth buyer network typically achieves better prices. Many serious sellers list on both.\"}}, {\"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"Do .ai domains sell better at auction or for fixed price?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"Both formats work. Fixed-price sales dominate volume on Namecheap and Dan.com, while auction formats on Sedo and GoDaddy tend to feature more premium domains. For short, brandable .ai domains, auctions can drive prices above expectations through bidder competition.\"}}]}", "schema_article": "{\"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"Article\", \"headline\": \"Best Platforms to Buy and Sell .ai Domains in 2026 (Ranked)\", \"description\": \"Compare the top .ai domain marketplaces \\u2014 Sedo, GoDaddy, Afternic, Dan.com, Brandforce & Spaceship \\u2014 for buyers and sellers. Real data, real fees, real sales.\", \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"NameBuzz Research Team\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"NameBuzz\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://namebuzz.co/logo.png\"}}, \"datePublished\": \"2026-04-14\", \"dateModified\": \"2026-04-14\", \"image\": [\"https://namebuzz.co/images/articles/best-ai-domain-platforms-comparison-2026-hero.jpg\"], \"articleSection\": \"Domain Investment\", \"keywords\": [\"ai domains\", \"buy ai domains\", \"sell ai domains\", \"sedo\", \"godaddy\", \"afternic\", \"namecheap\", \"dan.com\", \"ai domain marketplace\", \"ai domain fees\"]}", "content": "`## How We Ranked These Platforms\n\nOur rankings are based on analysis of the Namepros dataset covering 3,989 .ai domain sales across 40+ venues. We evaluated each platform against five criteria:\n\n| Criterion | Weight |\n|---|---|\n| Sales volume (buyer pool size) | 25% |\n| Average sale price achieved | 20% |\n| Fee structure transparency | 20% |\n| Seller tools and ease of listing | 20% |\n| Escrow and transaction security | 15% |\n\nWe also cross-referenced our findings against real-world sales documented on [Sedo's AI domain sales history](/blog/sedo-ai-domain-sales-history), [GoDaddy's auction results](/blog/godaddy-ai-domain-auctions-guide), and our broader [AI domain investment guide](/blog/ai-domain-investment-guide-2026).\n\n---\n\n## Best Marketplaces for Buying .ai Domains\n\nBuying a .ai domain is different from buying a .com. The buyer pool is more specialized, prices are less standardized, and negotiating tactics vary by platform. Here is how the major venues compare for buyers.\n\n### Sedo\n\n**Best for:** Buyers seeking premium, brandable .ai domains with transaction security\n\nSedo is the largest domain marketplace in the world by any measure, with over 40 million domains listed and a transaction history spanning more than two decades. For .ai domains, Sedo has established itself as the venue of choice for high-value transactions.\n\nNotable .ai sales on Sedo include **law.ai** at $350,000, and the platform has a dedicated \"AI Domains\" curated section that makes it easy for buyers to browse the premium end of the market.\n\n\n\nFor buyers, Sedo offers:\n\n- **SedoMLS** — a network of over 600 registrars and resellers who can present your domain to their customers\n- **Offer/Counter-offer system** — standard for domain negotiations\n- **Sedo Escrow** — protects both parties by holding funds until domain transfer is confirmed\n- **Domain buy now prices** — many listings have fixed prices, eliminating negotiation\n\nThe main downside for buyers is that Sedo's premium positioning means prices tend to be higher here than on volume-driven platforms like Namecheap.\n\n### GoDaddy Auctions\n\n**Best for:** Buyers who want high traffic and lots of inventory to choose from\n\nGoDaddy Auctions handles an enormous volume of domain sales across all extensions, and .ai domains are a growing part of their inventory. The platform's main advantage is traffic: GoDaddy's domain landing pages receive millions of visitors per month, giving listings strong organic visibility.\n\nThe dataset shows **cloud.ai** sold for a remarkable $600,000 through GoDaddy — one of the highest-recorded .ai sales in the entire dataset. This demonstrates that GoDaddy's buyer pool can include serious, well-capitalized buyers.\n\n\n\nGoDaddy also offers:\n\n- **GoDaddy Auctions+broad distribution** — listings can opt into GoDaddy's partner network\n- **MorningBidder** — a 5-day close auction format popular for domains with bidding interest\n- **Buy It Now** — fixed-price listings alongside auction-format sales\n- **Transfer and escrow included** — streamlined checkout for domain purchases\n\nBuyers should be aware that GoDaddy's fee structure is less transparent than some competitors, and the platform is known more for high-volume transactions than for premium curation.\n\n### Afternic\n\n**Best for:** Buyers who want access to a wide wholesale network without browsing dozens of individual platforms\n\nAfternic operates primarily as a distribution network — when you list on Afternic, your domain becomes visible across GoDaddy's massive partner ecosystem simultaneously. For buyers, this means Afternic is effectively a one-stop shop where you can find domains listed by sellers across the Afternic network.\n\n\n\nThe platform's **Fast Transfer** system is a major plus for buyers: once you win a domain, the transfer process is expedited, reducing the 5-7 day wait typical of manual registrar transfers.\n\nAfternic's notable .ai sales include **boyfriend.ai** at $230,000 and **breeze.ai** at $225,000, showing the platform can attract buyers for meaningful sales.\n\n### Dan.com\n\nDan.com, owned by GoDaddy, offers a different model: fixed-price listings with a focus on affordability and payment flexibility. Dan allows sellers to offer **installment plans**, which can make higher-priced .ai domains accessible to buyers who cannot pay a lump sum.\n\n\n\nFor buyers, Dan.com's advantage is its pricing transparency — no haggling, no auction format, just a stated price with an option to pay over time. This appeals to startup buyers and small businesses who want a .ai domain without the overhead of an auction process.\n\n### Namecheap\n\n**Best for:** Buyers seeking mid-market .ai domains at competitive prices, and those who already hold domains at Namecheap\n\nNamecheap processed 2,514 of the 3,989 .ai domain sales in the Namepros dataset — a staggering 63% share of all recorded transactions. This is not because Namecheap is the \"best\" platform in the abstract; it is because Namecheap has become the default venue for mid-market .ai domain transactions in the $1,000–$10,000 range.\n\nThe platform offers:\n\n- **Low 4.5% commission rate** for Namecheap marketplace sales\n- **Afternic integration** — Namecheap sellers can opt into the Afternic distribution network\n- **Quick transfers** — streamlined bulk transfer tools for investors managing multiple domains\n- **Premium .ai domain search** — dedicated search interface for .ai extensions\n\nNotable Namecheap .ai sale from the dataset: **blockchain.ai** at $405,000 — one of the highest in the entire dataset.\n\n### Spaceship.com\n\n**Best for:** Buyers looking for newer or less conventional .ai domains, and those interested in Spaceship's bundle pricing\n\nSpaceship.com is a newer entrant to the domain marketplace space, positioned as a more modern alternative to legacy registrars. The platform processed 123 .ai domain sales in the dataset, with **rank.ai** selling for $200,000 and **terafab.ai** at $174,257.\n\n\n\nSpaceship's appeal to buyers is its competitive pricing on registration and transfer, plus a curated approach to .ai listings that tends toward shorter, more brandable names.\n\n---\n\n## Best Platforms for Selling .ai Domains\n\nIf you are a seller, your calculus is different. You want the platform that will: (1) put your domain in front of the most qualified buyers, (2) achieve the highest possible price, and (3) minimize your fees. Here is how the major platforms stack up for sellers.\n\n### Sedo\n\nSedo is arguably the best platform for sellers with premium .ai domains. The combination of brand recognition, high-net-worth buyer pool, and robust transaction infrastructure means your domain gets the best possible chance of selling at its full value.\n\nKey seller features on Sedo:\n\n- **Sedo's domain appraisal service** — free automated valuation for all listings\n- **Sedo Pro** — premium listing placement for a higher commission rate, but better visibility\n- **Price reduction notifications** — buyers can opt in to be notified if your price drops\n- **SedoMLS distribution** — your listing goes to 600+ partner sites automatically\n- **Dedicated account managers** available for high-value portfolios\n\nThe trade-off is Sedo's commission, which runs up to 15% for standard accounts. However, for domains priced above $5,000, Sedo's buyer quality typically justifies the higher cut.\n\n### Afternic\n\nAfternic's strength for sellers is distribution breadth. Listing on Afternic automatically enters your domain into the Afternic network, which includes GoDaddy and hundreds of other registrar partner sites. This multiplies your exposure without requiring you to manage multiple accounts.\n\nFor sellers, Afternic offers:\n\n- **GoDaddy Auctions integration** — your listing also appears on GoDaddy\n- **7-day Fast Transfer** for completed transactions\n- **Customizable pricing** — buy-it-now, offer-only, or auction formats\n- **Afternic's Cash Offer program** — buyers can submit guaranteed cash offers\n\nCommission rates on Afternic typically run 3–5% for most sellers, making it one of the more cost-effective high-volume platforms.\n\n### GoDaddy Auctions\n\nGoDaddy's massive traffic makes it attractive for sellers, particularly those with mid-market domains. The platform's auction format can work in your favor if there is genuine competition for your domain, driving the final price above your expectations.\n\nSeller tools include:\n\n- **GoDaddy Auctions Pro** — higher placement and reduced fees for frequent sellers\n- **GoDaddy Cash Parking** — monetize low-value traffic domains while waiting for buyers\n- **BIN (Buy It Now) option** alongside auctions\n- **Portfolio management tools** for investors with multiple domains\n\nGoDaddy's commission on .ai sales is in the 10–17% range, which is on the higher side. However, the platform's traffic advantage can offset this for domains in the $2,000–$20,000 range.\n\n### Dan.com\n\nFor sellers who want simplicity and fixed pricing, Dan.com is a solid choice. Sellers list a fixed price, and buyers either accept it or they do not. No auction complexity, no bid management.\n\nDan.com is particularly well-suited for .ai domains priced between $1,000 and $10,000, where the installment payment option can help buyers afford your domain and close faster than they might through an escrow-heavy auction process.\n\nDan.com takes a 3% commission on completed sales.\n\n### Brandforce\n\nBrandforce is a domain aftermarket platform that focuses on brandable, premium domain names across a range of extensions, including .ai. It offers sellers a curated marketplace with built-in buyer discovery tools and streamlined transfer processes.\n\nBased on the Namepros dataset of 3,989 .ai domain sales, no transactions were recorded through Brandforce — suggesting that as of 2026, Brandforce had not yet established significant .ai domain trading volume. For sellers with .ai domains, this means the platform currently offers limited buyer activity compared to established venues like Sedo, Afternic, or Namecheap. If Brandforce expands its .ai domain inventory and buyer base in future, it may become worth revisiting for premium brand-name portfolios.\n\n\n### Spaceship.com\n\nSpaceship.com is an emerging option for .ai domain sellers who want competitive commission rates and a modern platform experience. Spaceship's commission structure is among the lowest at approximately 3–5%, and the platform is actively growing its .ai domain inventory.\n\nFor sellers with portfolios of mid-market .ai domains, Spaceship.com is worth adding to your multi-platform listing strategy.\n\n---\n\n## Platform Fees Compared\n\nUnderstanding fees is essential for calculating your actual return on a .ai domain sale. Here is a comparison of commission rates across the major platforms:\n\n\n\n| Platform | Buyer Fees | Seller Commission | Escrow Included | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Sedo** | 0% | 8–15% | Yes | Discounted rates for high-volume sellers |\n| **Afternic** | 0% | 3–5% | Yes | +GoDaddy partner distribution included |\n| **GoDaddy Auctions** | 0% | 10–17% | Yes | Reduced rates for Auctions Pro members |\n| **Dan.com** | 0% | 3% | Yes | Fixed pricing model, no auctions |\n| **Namecheap** | 0% | 4.5% | Yes | Can combine with Afternic network |\n| **Spaceship.com** | 0% | 3–5% | Yes | Modern platform, growing .ai volume |\n| **Dynadot** | 0% | 5–8% | Yes | Marketplace + private sales support |\n\n**Key insight:** Buyer fees are effectively zero across all major platforms — sellers bear the full commission cost. However, some platforms (notably Afternic and Namecheap) offer distribution network exposure that can justify their commission rates through higher sale probabilities.\n\nFor a domain selling at the median price of **$2,215** (based on the Namepros dataset), even a 3% difference in commission equals $67. For a premium domain selling at $200,000, that same 3% difference equals $6,000. Platform choice matters more at higher price points.\n\n---\n\n## Which Platform Has the Most .ai Sales?\n\nThis is where the Namepros dataset tells a compelling story. Of 3,989 .ai domain sales recorded on Namepros across 40+ venues, here is the volume distribution:\n\n\n\n| Platform | Recorded Sales | Share of Dataset |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Namecheap** | 2,514 | 63.0% |\n| **Dynadot** | 849 | 21.3% |\n| **Atom.com** | 143 | 3.6% |\n| **Spaceship.com** | 123 | 3.1% |\n| **Afternic** | 106 | 2.7% |\n| **Whois.ai** | 86 | 2.2% |\n| **Sedo** | 52 | 1.3% |\n| **Private** | 33 | 0.8% |\n| **Brands.io** | 16 | 0.4% |\n| **DAN.com** | 13 | 0.3% |\n| **GoDaddy** | 5 | 0.1% |\n\nTwo patterns immediately emerge from this data:\n\n**First, Namecheap and Dynadot dominate volume.** These two platforms account for 84% of all recorded .ai Namepros sales. This is not necessarily because they offer the best prices — it is because they are accessible, affordable, and have built massive buyer and seller communities over many years.\n\n**Second, the \"premium\" platforms (Sedo, Afternic, GoDaddy) account for a small volume but disproportionate share of high-value sales.** Sedo's 52 recorded sales include law.ai at $350,000. Afternic's 106 sales include boyfriend.ai at $230,000 and breeze.ai at $225,000. GoDaddy's 5 recorded sales include cloud.ai at $600,000. These outliers are not random noise — they reflect the fact that buyers who go to Sedo, Afternic, or GoDaddy are often more serious, better-capitalized buyers than the typical Namecheap buyer.\n\nThe lesson for sellers: **use Namecheap or Dynadot for volume and quick turnover of mid-market .ai domains, but list your best assets on Sedo, Afternic, or GoDaddy where serious buyers are waiting.**\n\n---\n\n## Our Ranking Verdict\n\nAfter analyzing 3,989 .ai domain sales data, cross-referencing against our existing platform guides, and evaluating fee structures and buyer pools, here is our 2026 ranking verdict:\n\n### For Buyers\n\n1. **Namecheap** — Best for mid-market .ai domains ($1,000–$10,000). Huge inventory, competitive prices, and the largest recorded sales volume of any platform.\n2. **Sedo** — Best for premium .ai domains ($50,000+). The platform attracts serious buyers and has the infrastructure for high-value transactions.\n3. **Afternic** — Best for access to the broadest network. One listing reaches GoDaddy and 600+ partner sites.\n4. **GoDaddy Auctions** — Best for auction-style buying where competition can drive price discovery.\n5. **Dan.com** — Best for buyers who want installment payment options.\n\n### For Sellers\n\n1. **Sedo** — Best for premium domains where brand and buyer quality matter more than volume.\n2. **Afternic + Namecheap dual listing** — Best strategy for mid-market sellers. Namecheap's volume plus Afternic's network reach.\n3. **Namecheap** — Best for high-volume, lower-priced .ai domains where you want quick turnover.\n4. **GoDaddy Auctions** — Best when you have bidding competition from a well-trafficked platform.\n5. **Dan.com** — Best for sellers with domains priced under $10,000 who want a simple fixed-price process.\n6. **Spaceship.com** — Best emerging platform for sellers willing to try newer venues.\n\nThe optimal strategy for most .ai domain investors in 2026 is a **dual-listing approach**: list your premium .ai domains on both Sedo and Afternic simultaneously, and use Namecheap or Dynadot for faster mid-market turnover. Our [AI domain investment guide](/blog/ai-domain-investment-guide-2026) covers portfolio building strategies in more detail.\n\nFor the highest recorded .ai domain sale in the dataset — **cloud.ai at $600,000** through GoDaddy — we also recommend reviewing [the biggest .ai domain sales ever recorded](/blog/biggest-ai-domain-sales-ever) for context on what drives these extraordinary valuations.\n\n---\n\n## Frequently Asked Questions\n\n### Which platform has the lowest fees for selling .ai domains?\n\nDan.com has the lowest commission at 3%, followed by Namecheap at 4.5% and Afternic at 3–5%. However, lower fees do not automatically mean higher net returns — platforms with higher fees like Sedo (8–15%) often attract buyers willing to pay significantly more for premium domains. Calculate your expected net on each platform before deciding where to list.\n\n### Can I list my .ai domain on multiple platforms at the same time?\n\nYes, and for most sellers this is the recommended strategy. You can list on Namecheap and simultaneously opt into the Afternic distribution network. You can also list on both Sedo and Afternic. Just make sure your pricing is consistent across platforms to avoid confusing buyers or creating arbitrage situations.\n\n### What is the average sale price for a .ai domain?\n\nBased on 3,989 recorded .ai domain sales from the Namepros dataset, the **median sale price is $2,215** and the **average (mean) sale price is $9,433**. The wide gap between median and average reflects the heavy right tail of the distribution — a small number of very high-value sales ($200,000–$750,000) that pull the average up significantly. 90% of all .ai domain sales fall below $20,000.\n\n### Is Sedo or GoDaddy better for selling .ai domains?\n\nIt depends on the value of your domain. For domains priced under $10,000, GoDaddy's traffic advantage can help you find a buyer faster. For domains priced above $50,000, Sedo's reputation and high-net-worth buyer network typically achieves better prices. Many serious sellers list on both.\n\n### Do .ai domains sell better at auction or for fixed price?\n\nThe data shows both formats work. Fixed-price sales through Dan.com and Namecheap dominate volume, while auction-style sales on Sedo and GoDaddy tend to feature more premium domains. If your .ai domain is short, brandable, and clearly valuable, an auction format can create competition that drives the price above your expectations. If you have a realistic market valuation in mind, a fixed-price listing reduces uncertainty.\n\n---\n\n## Sources & Methodology\n\n1. **Namepros .ai Domain Sales Dataset (2026)** — 3,989 recorded .ai domain sales across 40+ venues, analyzed for venue distribution, price ranges, and top sales. Source: \\`/shared-memory/team2/namebuzz_namepros_scrape_V2.xlsx\\`\n2. **Sedo AI Domain Sales History** — NameBuzz Research Team analysis of Sedo's transaction records and notable .ai sales. [namebuzz.co](/blog/sedo-ai-domain-sales-history)\n3. **GoDaddy Auctions Guide** — NameBuzz Research Team. [namebuzz.co](/blog/godaddy-ai-domain-auctions-guide)\n4. **AI Domain Investment Guide 2026** — NameBuzz Research Team covering platform strategy and portfolio building. [namebuzz.co](/blog/ai-domain-investment-guide-2026)\n5. **Biggest .ai Domain Sales Ever** — NameBuzz Research Team documenting record-breaking .ai transactions. [namebuzz.co](/blog/biggest-ai-domain-sales-ever)`"},
{"slug": "sedo-vs-godaddy-vs-afternic-ai-domains", "title": "Sedo vs GoDaddy vs Afternic for .ai Domains — Which Platform Wins in 2026?", "date": "2026-04-14", "description": "Sedo wins for high-value premium .ai domains, handling sales like law.ai ($350,000) with a buyer pool that includes serious AI companies and investors. GoDaddy leads on raw traffic volume and auction drama, achieving the dataset's highest .ai sale at $600,000 for cloud.ai. Afternic is the best wholesale distributor — one listing reaches GoDaddy's entire partner network simultaneously, making it the most efficient for sellers who want maximum exposure without managing multiple accounts.", "readTime": "12 min read", "author": "NameBuzz Research Team", "schema_faq": "{\"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"FAQPage\", \"mainEntity\": [{\"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"Which platform is best for selling .ai domains worth over $100,000?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"Sedo is the best platform for six-figure .ai domain sales. Its buyer pool consists of serious buyers \\u2014 AI companies, investors, and established businesses. Sedo's escrow and transaction infrastructure is battle-tested for high-value deals, and the platform's reputation gives both parties confidence. For a $100,000+ .ai sale, Sedo's 10\\u201315% commission is worth the price for added security and buyer quality.\"}}, {\"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"Can I list on Sedo, GoDaddy, and Afternic at the same time?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"Yes, and this is the strategy recommended by most professional domain investors. Do not list the same domain at different prices simultaneously \\u2014 this creates arbitrage confusion. Instead, choose a primary platform and price, and use the others for distribution. Some sellers use Sedo as the primary auction venue while maintaining an Afternic listing with a higher Buy It Now price as a fallback.\"}}, {\"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"Does GoDaddy have the most buyers for .ai domains?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"GoDaddy has the most raw traffic, but 'most traffic' does not always mean 'best buyers.' The Namepros dataset shows only 5 of 3,989 recorded .ai sales came through GoDaddy, compared to Namecheap's 2,514. This likely reflects limited data capture rather than weakness \\u2014 cloud.ai sold for $600,000 on GoDaddy, proving serious buyers do transact there. GoDaddy should be part of a multi-platform strategy.\"}}, {\"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"What fees should I expect when selling a .ai domain?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"All major platforms charge sellers a commission: Sedo 8\\u201315%, GoDaddy 10\\u201317%, Afternic 3\\u20135%, Namecheap 4.5%, Dan.com 3%. Buyer fees are zero across all platforms. Escrow and transfer are included at no extra charge on all major platforms. For a $10,000 .ai domain sale, expect to net $8,500\\u2013$9,550 depending on your platform.\"}}, {\"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"How long does it take to sell a .ai domain on these platforms?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"Mid-market .ai domains ($1,000\\u2013$10,000) on Namecheap or Afternic typically sell within 30\\u201390 days. Premium domains ($50,000+) on Sedo may take 3\\u201312 months. Auction formats can accelerate the process if multiple buyers compete. Domains priced realistically for their quality sell faster than overpriced domains regardless of platform.\"}}]}", "schema_article": "{\"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"Article\", \"headline\": \"Sedo vs GoDaddy vs Afternic for .ai Domains \\u2014 Which Platform Wins in 2026?\", \"description\": \"Direct comparison of Sedo, GoDaddy and Afternic for .ai domain transactions. Fees, buyer volume, sale prices, and which platform actually gets domains sold.\", \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"NameBuzz Research Team\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"NameBuzz\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://namebuzz.co/logo.png\"}}, \"datePublished\": \"2026-04-14\", \"dateModified\": \"2026-04-14\", \"image\": [\"https://namebuzz.co/images/articles/sedo-godaddy-afternic-comparison-banner-2026.jpg\"], \"articleSection\": \"Domain Investment\", \"keywords\": [\"sedo ai domains\", \"godaddy ai domains\", \"afternic ai domains\", \"ai domain comparison\", \"sell ai domain\", \"ai domain platform fees\", \"ai domain marketplace\"]}", "content": "`## Sedo — The Premium Auction House\n\nSedo calls itself the world's largest domain marketplace, and with over 40 million listed domains and two decades of transaction history, it is hard to argue. For .ai domain sellers specifically, Sedo has earned its reputation as the premium venue — the place where serious buyers go when they want a serious .ai domain and are willing to pay for it.\n\n### Who is on Sedo?\n\nSedo attracts a mix of domain investors (people who buy and sell domains professionally), AI startups looking for brandable domains, and occasionally large corporates acquiring strategic domain names. The platform is global, with significant buyer activity from North America, Europe, and Asia.\n\nThe type of buyer you find on Sedo tends to be more informed and more motivated than the average domain marketplace browser. They have usually done their research, know what comparable domains are worth, and are approaching the purchase as a business investment rather than an impulse buy.\n\n### Notable .ai Sales on Sedo\n\nThe Namepros dataset records 52 .ai sales through Sedo, including:\n\n- **law.ai** — $350,000. A single-word .ai domain in a high-value legal industry vertical.\n- Multiple additional six-figure .ai sales across the dataset.\n\nThe Sedo average sale price for .ai domains is notably higher than the overall dataset median of $2,215, reflecting the platform's premium positioning.\n\n\n\n### Fees on Sedo\n\nSedo's commission structure for sellers:\n\n- **Standard account:** 8–15% commission on completed sales\n- **Sedo Pro account:** Reduced commission rates for high-volume sellers (negotiated)\n- **Buy It Now listings:** Commission on the listed price\n- **Auction listings:** Commission on the winning bid\n- **Transfer and escrow:** Included at no additional charge\n\nFor a $100,000 .ai sale, a 10% Sedo commission equals $10,000. That is significant, but compared to selling through a broker (typically 10–15% plus engagement fees), Sedo's direct marketplace model remains competitive.\n\n### Key Seller Features\n\n- **SedoMLS Distribution Network** — Your listing is automatically broadcast to 600+ partner registrars and resellers worldwide\n- **Sedo Domain Appraisal** — Free automated valuation to help you set competitive pricing\n- **Make Offer / Buy Now hybrid** — List a price but also accept offers below it\n- **Auction formats** — 1-day, 3-day, 5-day, 7-day, and 10-day auctions\n- **Sedo Financing** — Buyers can pay in installments, which can increase the pool of qualified buyers for expensive domains\n\nSedo is best suited for .ai domains with an estimated value above $10,000. Below that threshold, the commission bite becomes proportionally larger and Namecheap or Afternic may achieve similar outcomes with lower fees.\n\n---\n\n## GoDaddy Auctions — The High-Volume Marketplace\n\nGoDaddy needs no introduction. With over 84 million domain names under management and a dominant share of the domain registration market, GoDaddy Auctions is the highest-traffic domain sales platform in the world by raw visitor numbers.\n\nFor .ai domain sellers, GoDaddy Auctions offers volume and visibility. The platform's auction format, combined with its enormous organic traffic, means your domain gets seen by more people more quickly than on almost any other venue.\n\n### Who is on GoDaddy?\n\nGoDaddy's buyer pool is broad and varied. You will find first-time domain buyers, small business owners, startup founders, domain investors, and occasional corporate buyers. The volume is real — GoDaddy processes more domain transactions per day than most registrars process in a year.\n\nThe diversity of GoDaddy's buyer pool cuts both ways. On one hand, it means more potential buyers for your .ai domain. On the other hand, the average GoDaddy buyer may be less sophisticated about domain valuation than a Sedo buyer, which can affect negotiation dynamics.\n\n### Notable .ai Sales on GoDaddy\n\nThe Namepros dataset records just 5 .ai sales through GoDaddy — but what these five lack in volume they make up for in value:\n\n- **cloud.ai** — $600,000. The single highest .ai domain sale in the entire 3,989-record dataset.\n\nThis extraordinary result shows that GoDaddy's buyer pool can include exceptionally well-capitalized buyers. The $600,000 cloud.ai sale demonstrates that the platform is not just for mid-market transactions — it can handle significant deals when the right buyer shows up.\n\n\n\n### Fees on GoDaddy\n\nGoDaddy Auctions commission rates:\n\n- **Standard listings:** 12–17% commission on winning bids\n- **GoDaddy Auctions Pro:** Reduced rates for frequent sellers (starts at 10%)\n- **Buy It Now listings:** Similar commission structure\n- **GoDaddy Cash Parking:** For domains not yet listed for sale — earn revenue from GoDaddy-served parking page ads while waiting for the right buyer\n- **Transfer fees:** Included with most sales\n\nGoDaddy's fees are on the higher end for domain sales platforms. However, the platform's auction model can sometimes drive final prices above expectations through natural competition among bidders.\n\n### Key Seller Features\n\n- **GoDaddy Auctions+broad distribution** — Listings can be broadcast across GoDaddy's partner network for additional exposure\n- **Multiple auction formats** — MorningBidder (5-day close), 7-day auctions, and 10-day auctions\n- **Reserve price option** — Set a minimum price below which you are not obligated to sell\n- **GoDaddy appraisal tool** — Free valuation estimates to guide your listing price\n- **Parking and monetization** — Domains can earn parking revenue while listed\n\n---\n\n## Afternic — The Wholesale Distribution Network\n\nAfternic is unique among the three giants in that it functions primarily as a distribution layer rather than a standalone marketplace. When you list a domain on Afternic, your listing becomes visible not just on Afternic.com, but across GoDaddy's entire partner network — hundreds of registrar and reseller websites that display Afternic-listed domains to their customers.\n\nThis makes Afternic extraordinarily efficient for sellers: one listing, maximum distribution.\n\n### Who is on Afternic?\n\nAfternic buyers are a hybrid of the GoDaddy and Sedo buyer pools. Because Afternic listings appear on GoDaddy's main platform (GoDaddy acquired Afternic in 2021), you get exposure to GoDaddy's high-traffic buyer base. At the same time, Afternic's curated approach attracts buyers who are specifically looking for well-valued domains across multiple registrars.\n\nAfternic's buyer network includes individual domain investors, startup founders, and small businesses looking for brandable domains at various price points.\n\n### Notable .ai Sales on Afternic\n\nThe Namepros dataset records 106 .ai sales through Afternic, including several notable high-value transactions:\n\n- **boyfriend.ai** — $230,000\n- **breeze.ai** — $225,000\n- **zip.ai** — $200,000\n\nThese results demonstrate that Afternic attracts serious buyers willing to pay six figures for the right .ai domain.\n\n\n\n### Fees on Afternic\n\nAfternic's commission structure:\n\n- **Standard account:** 3–5% commission on completed sales\n- **Fast Transfer included:** Expedited domain transfer process at no extra charge\n- **No listing fees** — listing your domain on Afternic is free\n- **Afternic Cash Offer program:** Buyers submit guaranteed cash offers backed by Afternic, giving sellers confidence in transaction completion\n\nAt 3–5%, Afternic's commission is among the lowest of any major .ai domain platform — lower than Sedo, significantly lower than GoDaddy.\n\n### Key Seller Features\n\n- **Automatic GoDaddy distribution** — Your Afternic listing appears on GoDaddy Auctions simultaneously\n- **Fast Transfer system** — Reduces standard 5–7 day transfer timeline\n- **Price flexibility** — Buy It Now, Make Offer, or auction formats\n- **Afternic Cash Offer** — Guaranteed buyer's offer option for faster closes\n- **International reach** — Distribution across global registrar partners, not just US-based\n\n---\n\n## Side-by-Side Comparison Table\n\n\n\n| Feature | Sedo | GoDaddy Auctions | Afternic |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Commission rate** | 8–15% | 10–17% | 3–5% |\n| **Buyer traffic** | Moderate-high | Highest | Moderate (via GoDaddy) |\n| **Best for domain value** | $10,000+ | $1,000–$600,000 | $5,000+ |\n| **Escrow included** | Yes | Yes | Yes (Fast Transfer) |\n| **Auction formats** | Yes (1–10 day) | Yes (5–10 day) | Yes |\n| **Distribution network** | SedoMLS (600+ partners) | GoDaddy partner network | GoDaddy + 600+ partners |\n| **Installment payments** | Sedo Financing | Via GoDaddy Pay | Afternic Cash Offer |\n| **Listing fees** | None | None | None |\n| **Notable .ai sale** | law.ai ($350,000) | cloud.ai ($600,000) | boyfriend.ai ($230,000) |\n| **Recorded .ai sales (dataset)** | 52 | 5 | 106 |\n| **Average price level** | High | Variable | Medium-high |\n\n---\n\n## Which Platform Gets Higher Prices?\n\nThis is the question every .ai domain seller wants answered. Based on the data, the honest answer is: **it depends, but Sedo and Afternic consistently attract higher per-sale prices while GoDaddy wins on raw transaction volume.**\n\n\n\nHere is the data breakdown from the Namepros dataset:\n\n**Sedo (52 recorded sales):** Despite the smallest volume of the three, Sedo's recorded sales include some of the highest-value .ai transactions in the dataset. The platform's premium buyer pool — buyers who specifically go to Sedo looking for valuable domains — creates a price ceiling that Namecheap and Dynadot simply cannot match.\n\n**Afternic (106 recorded sales):** Afternic's sales span a wide range from the $1,000s to $230,000. The platform's distribution advantage means more eyes on your domain, and the data shows this translates to strong average prices. boyfriend.ai at $230,000, breeze.ai at $225,000, and zip.ai at $200,000 all came through Afternic.\n\n**GoDaddy (5 recorded sales):** GoDaddy's recorded volume is small in the dataset (5 sales), but the $600,000 cloud.ai transaction is the highest .ai sale in the entire 3,989-record dataset. This is likely not representative of GoDaddy's average sale price — it likely reflects a specific high-stakes negotiation — but it proves that GoDaddy's buyer pool is capable of extraordinary transactions.\n\n**The practical insight:** If you are selling a premium, brandable .ai domain with a realistic valuation above $25,000, Sedo or Afternic are your best shots at maximizing the sale price. If you have a mid-market .ai domain and want the highest probability of selling within 30–60 days, a dual Afternic + Namecheap listing is the most efficient strategy.\n\nFor more context on what .ai domains have sold for historically, see our article on the [biggest .ai domain sales ever](/blog/biggest-ai-domain-sales-ever) and the [Sedo AI domain sales history](/blog/sedo-ai-domain-sales-history).\n\n---\n\n## Which Should You List On? (Decision Framework)\n\nRather than giving you a simple \"winner,\" here is the actual decision framework based on your profile and domain:\n\n\n\n\n\n### You have a premium .ai domain (estimated value $50,000+)\n\n**List on Sedo.** The platform's reputation, high-net-worth buyer pool, and transaction infrastructure are purpose-built for this price range. Use Sedo's auction format with a 7 or 10-day window to maximize visibility and competition. Consider also adding an Afternic listing simultaneously for additional distribution.\n\n### You have a mid-market .ai domain (estimated value $10,000–$50,000)\n\n**List on Afternic + GoDaddy simultaneously.** Afternic gives you the 3–5% commission rate plus GoDaddy distribution. GoDaddy adds additional traffic and auction exposure. Together, these two platforms give you maximum buyer coverage at a reasonable commission cost.\n\n### You have a standard .ai domain (estimated value $1,000–$10,000)\n\n**List on Namecheap with Afternic network opt-in.** Namecheap's 4.5% commission and enormous volume of .ai domain buyers means you have the highest probability of a quick sale at a fair price. Enable the Afternic distribution network from within Namecheap to get GoDaddy's buyer pool without managing a separate Afternic account.\n\n### You want the fastest possible sale\n\n**List on GoDaddy Auctions with a Buy It Now price set at market rate.** GoDaddy's traffic volume creates the highest daily buyer exposure. Combined with the Afternic Fast Transfer system, you can close a transaction in under a week from listing to transfer.\n\n### You want maximum price on a premium domain\n\n**List on Sedo with an auction format and a reserve price.** Set your reserve (minimum acceptable price) at your floor valuation. If the auction does not hit your reserve, you are no worse off than listing at a fixed price — but if two serious buyers compete, you could achieve a price well above your expectations.\n\n### You have multiple .ai domains\n\n**Use a multi-platform strategy:** List premium domains on Sedo, mid-market domains on Afternic + GoDaddy, and volume/standard domains on Namecheap. This is how professional .ai domain investors maximize their portfolio returns.\n\nOur [AI domain investment guide](/blog/ai-domain-investment-guide-2026) covers portfolio strategy and multi-platform management in detail.\n\n---\n\n## Frequently Asked Questions\n\n### Which platform is best for selling .ai domains worth over $100,000?\n\nSedo is the best platform for six-figure .ai domain sales. Its buyer pool consists of serious buyers — AI companies, investors, and established businesses — who are comfortable with high-value transactions. Sedo's escrow and transaction infrastructure is battle-tested for deals in this range, and the platform's reputation gives both parties confidence. For a $100,000+ .ai sale, Sedo's 10–15% commission is worth the price for the added security and buyer quality.\n\n### Can I list on Sedo, GoDaddy, and Afternic at the same time?\n\nYes, and this is the strategy recommended by most professional domain investors. However, you should not list the same domain at different prices on different platforms simultaneously — this creates arbitrage confusion. Instead, choose a primary listing platform and price, and use the others for distribution. Some sellers use Sedo as the primary auction platform while also maintaining an Afternic listing with a higher Buy It Now price as a fallback.\n\n### Does GoDaddy have the most buyers for .ai domains?\n\nGoDaddy has the most raw traffic of any domain platform, but \"most traffic\" does not always mean \"best buyers for .ai domains.\" The Namepros dataset shows that despite GoDaddy's enormous volume, only 5 of 3,989 recorded .ai sales came through GoDaddy — a tiny fraction compared to Namecheap's 2,514. This does not mean GoDaddy is weak; it likely means that many GoDaddy .ai sales are not captured in the Namepros thread dataset. For sellers, GoDaddy should be part of a multi-platform strategy rather than a standalone venue.\n\n### What fees should I expect when selling a .ai domain?\n\nAll major platforms charge the seller a commission on completed sales. Expected ranges: Sedo 8–15%, GoDaddy 10–17%, Afternic 3–5%, Namecheap 4.5%, Dan.com 3%. Buyer fees are zero across all platforms. Escrow and transfer services are included at no additional charge on all major platforms. For a $10,000 .ai domain sale, expect to net $8,500–$9,550 depending on your platform, before any applicable taxes.\n\n### How long does it take to sell a .ai domain on these platforms?\n\nThere is no guaranteed timeline, but the data gives useful context. Mid-market .ai domains ($1,000–$10,000) on Namecheap or Afternic typically sell within 30–90 days at competitive prices. Premium domains ($50,000+) on Sedo may take 3–12 months to find the right buyer. Using an auction format on any platform can accelerate the process if multiple buyers compete. Domains priced realistically for their quality sell faster than overpriced domains regardless of platform.`"}
